-- France Plans to Open Capital of Four Regional Airports, Les Echos Reports
-- B y   D a v i d   W h i t e h o u s e
-- 2010-09-27T05:08:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/france-plans-to-open-capital-of-four-regional-airports-les-echos-reports.html
France has started a tender to seek
a bank to find new investors for four regional airports, Les
Echos reported, without saying where it got the information.  The government is planning to open the capital of Lyon,
Nice, Toulouse and Bordeaux airports up to a maximum level of 49
percent, according to the newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
